Stephen
kept looking at him, his eyes locked on Tony’s, and he didn’t say
a...
body:
For Snippet Sunday (from chapter 4 of Wildflowers):

Stephen kept looking at him, his eyes locked on Tony’s, and he didn’t say a word. It was as if he was taking Tony in, looking into his very soul. And maybe he was. Maybe he had realised what kind of a man Tony was—a selfish billionaire, a rich brat, a spoiled manchild. Someone you didn’t want a relationship with. Someone you kept around for the money and the benefits of having someone as a … friend … who was famous, who could open every door for you.

Yeah, maybe Stephen had realised that Tony was nothing special, that he wasn’t worth the trouble. Or maybe he had thought about what would happen if he did pursue a relationship with a celebrity. What it would mean for his own life. Privacy wouldn’t be a thing anymore.

summary: I wonder what's it like at 4 am on the very top of the stark tower. I mean, that's the time when it's usually too late to be...
body:
I wonder what’s it like at 4 am on the very top of the stark tower. I mean, that’s the time when it’s usually too late to be still awake, but also too early to be already up. It’s when you feel old and powerful but also tiny and naive, watching the sun rise or the stars begin to fade slowly. It’s the modern witching hour.

And I bet it’s beautiful, from up there.

Sadly enough, I think Tony could easily answer that question.
